, City of Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Scotland","Midlothian, Scotland":"Midlothian, Scotland","Edinburgh, City of Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Morrison","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: from <i>Ó Muirgheasáin</i> ‘descendant of <i>Muirgheasán</i>’, a diminutive of <i>Muirgheas</i>, a personal name meaning ‘sea valor’.","Scottish: from Gaelic <b>Mac Moireasdain</b> ‘son of <i>Moireasdan</i>’, a personal name cognate with Irish <i>Muirgheasán</i>’ (see 1 above).","Scottish and English: patronymic from the personal name   Morris  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Morrisson","meanings":["English: variant of   Morrison  ."]},{"name":"Morson","meanings":["English, Scottish and Irish: shortened form of   Morrison  .","English: sometimes a variant of <b>Moorsom</b>, a habitational name from Moorsholm in North Yorkshire. The placename derives from Old English <i>mōr</i> ‘moor’ + <i>hūsum</i>, dative plural form of <i>hūs</i> ‘house’."]},{"name":"Morison","meanings":["Scottish (northern): variant of   Morrison  ."]},{"name":"Morris","meanings":["English and Scottish: from <i>Maurice</i>, an Old French personal name introduced to Britain by the Normans. It is derived from Latin <i>Mauritius</i>, a derivative of <i>Maurus</i> (see   Moore  ). This was the name of several early Christian saints. In some cases it may be a nickname of the same derivation for someone with a swarthy complexion.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Muirghis</b>, a variant of <b>Ó Muirgheasa</b> (see   Morrissey  ).","Welsh: Anglicized form of the personal name <i>Meurig</i> (from Latin <i>Mauritius</i>), which was gradually superseded in Wales by <i>Morus</i>, <i>Morys</i>, a derivative of the Anglo-Norman French form of the name (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"McCorriston","meanings":["Scottish (Wigtownshire): probably from <b>Mac Thoireasdain</b> ‘son of <i>Tòireasdan</i> or <i>Tòrasdan</i>’, a Gaelicized form of the Old Norse name <i>Thórrsteinn</i> ‘thunder stone’. It may also be from a lenited form of Gaelic <b>Mac Moireasdain</b> ‘son of <i>Moireasdan</i>’; see   Morrison  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Morrison I was born in 1495, in Edinburgh, Scotland, his father, Ewen Morrison, was 21 and his mother, Margaret Peggy McInnes, was 17. He married Katherine Margaret Preston in 1517, in Edinburgh, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 3 daughters. He died in 1550, in Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 55, and was buried in Midlothian, Scotland."},"et":{"1495–1550":"1495–1550","1510–Female":"1510–Surnud","1500–1595":"1500–1595","1517–Female":"1517–Surnud","1520–1568":"1520–1568","1525–1568":"1525–1568","1530–1630":"1530–1630","1474–1521":"1474–1521","1478–1500":"1478–1500","1495":"1495","1550":"1550","1525":"1525","1568":"1568","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1520":"1520","1630":"1630","1530":"1530","1474":"1474","1595":"1595","1517":"1517","about 1494":"umbes 1494","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Scotland","Canongate, Edinburgh, City of Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Scotland","Midlothian, Scotland":"Midlothian, Scotland","Edinburgh, City of Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1495–1550":"1495–1550","1510–Female":"1510–Kuollut","1500–1595":"1500–1595","1517–Female":"1517–Kuollut","1520–1568":"1520–1568","1525–1568":"1525–1568","1530–1630":"1530–1630","1474–1521":"1474–1521","1478–1500":"1478–1500","1495":"1495","1550":"1550","1525":"1525","1568":"1568","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","152